review_blob: Pretty good beer, fresh and crisp, nice to eat with, not at the bar. low level of head to offer, nice golden color, good with chicken particularly.
Refreshing and smooth tasmanian beer, nice amber color and great crisp taste, good to just sit back and relax.

This is a pretty decent beer, although not my favorite, its up there. I would have to say that it has a full crisp taste altough there is a strong aroma to it, it is very good with a meat dish. I would recommend it.

I would say that this is good for those of us trying to cut down, but it really doesnt taste very good. Its kind of like a watered down Grasshopper with a bit of skunk and a lot less flavor. Better go with a godd beer like Grasshopper from Big Rock.
beer_name: Big Rock Jack Rabbit Low Carb Lager

review_blob: This is a very good cider that goes down smoothly and can be drunken with just about anything. I highly recommend it. It has a light yellow diamond color with a nonexistant head, but it has a great taste, very fresh and very refreshing.
beer_name: Big Rock Rock Creek Premium Dry Cider

review_blob: Not a fan, very watered down and not taste to it. Big Rock produces some great beers, but this is not one of them.

It is ok for a stout but defniately not as good as a Guiness draft in a Dublin pub, but then again, what is? I think that this is a good beer if you like stout and happen to be in Big Rock at the time, but I much prefer their Grasshopper, Warthog, or their Traditional.

I would have to say that this beer is a very smooth beer, maybe too smooth, and not enough taste to go with the smoothness. But thats ok, if you like watery beers this is the beer for you. If not, then just try it once, but I doubt youll be a return buyer if you dont like watery beers. In its defence it is alot better than alot of other watery beers that I know and I would prefer to drink it to budweiser, thats for sure.

This is a nice beer if you like strong ales. It is one of the most beautiful looking beers of its kind when poured correctly, with a nice amber color and a huge foamy head. It has a crisp taste and I must say a bit stronger than your average smooth ale, but not in a bad way. It does hide its 8.5% of alcohol very well, and does go down quite smoothly for its strength. It smells quite nice as well, a definite must try.

This one surprised me, it is quite smooth and easy to drink and the head stayed for a bit as well. It goes well with alot of different kinds of foods beacause its taste is fairly balanced, not too strong or bitter. Nice grainy taste and smell, the smell is fainter than the taste. It is subtle but striking. I would drink it regularly if I wasnt living in South Korea at the moment.

Its a pretty good beer, but big rock makes some better ones, in my opinion. I prefer grasshopper or warthog, myself. But this is not a bad beer for a switch from either of those once in a while if you are a big rock fan.

Nice brown color, incredably smooth. I was quite impressed because this is a beer that I could drink alot of if I was thirsty and it doesnt lose much. Good carbonation, nice taste, but the head was very thin, thats the 4 for appearance.
beer_name: Big Rock Warthog English Style Mild Ale

review_blob: This is a great beer. Its smooth and has a nice refreshing, and definately a bit full, mouthfeel. It has a good aroma with its own uniqueness to it. The taste is nice, with a fuirt and spice mixture in it, one that is more apparent in its aftertaste. I also felt that the color was a beautiful one, although dark for an ale. The head disappeared a bit faster than it should, although not in a too quick way, which caused a 4 instead of a five in appearance. Its one of the best beers, especially of its strength, Ive tasted so far, but Im still new to the Belgian ones. I felt it was a great beer that I would drink regularly, one that held true to its reputation of being a high quality Belgian Abbey Beer.
Damn good on draft! It is very smooth and thats included on the not so bitter aftertaste. I was quite impressed and I would definately drink it again.
UPDATED: MAR 30, 2008

I was thoroughly impressed by this beer, considering its a mexican beer. Definately the best mexican beer that Ive tried and one of the best mexican beers out there. So far I havent been happy with the mexican beer that Ive tasted, but this ones quite good. Nice color, the head doesnt disappear too fast, and it has a smooth, slighty sweet taste to it. Very acceptable feeling in the mouth.

It was quite good, it was smooth and easy to drink. Goes well with food, but not a high-end beer. Its a generic stout, and is slightly better than other generic beers around. I would take it over any korean beer or generic beer to date. The bitterness is surprisingly subtle and although its not a beer to try for outstanding taste, it still has a decent taste, better than what you can say for other generic beers.

Its better than Budweiser. Its not bad if you want to drink a beer, and dont want to enjoy a full flavored beer. It is an ok beer, best generic beer that Ive tried yet. Its not one for a celebration though. It goes down smooth and has just enough bitterness, but its a bit watered down for a full apreciable flavor. But what it has is ok for what it is, a generic beer.
Its a generic, cheap beer designed for those who want to get drunk cheaply. Enough said.

I must say that is was a big disappointment for being the number one beer of Australia. I thought that it was an overly bitter generic beer. Its a step up from Budweiser, but thats not a difficult thing to pull off.
Smooth all the way down. This beer is smooth, but filling, altough light at the same time. A well-rounded beer with a subtle, but nice taste. I quite enjoyed it.

Coopers pale ale is a bit salty with some citrus in it, like a salty lemon mixed with beer. Its quite a nice effect, many people werent impressed on this page but actually I liked it. I dont know, it might be my individual taste, but I would have it regularly if possible, although where I am it is expensive. Still, a great beer.

Samuel Adams is definately one of the best beers around. The color is a deep amber, it looks delicious. The taste is smooth and has hints of sweetness in the aroma. Frankly, I have to say that this beer tasted liked beer. It tastes the way that everybody has in their head as the way beer is supposed to taste like. A great beer by the makers of great beer, I enjoy many of Samuel Adams products, it can be said that I am a Samuel Adams guy.

I like Coopers, but the aftertaste on this one didnt settle well with me. As far as Stouts go, I prefer Guinness. Its still an ok beer, though, I expected a bit more. The mouth feel was alright, the alcohol seems a bit high for the bitterness that is given. The color is ok, but the head disappears rapidly. The aftertaste is a bit too much in the bitterness category, which takes away from the experience. It is quite smooth, however on going down.
UPDATED: OCT 4, 2007
